narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This professor won't be returning. The class was usually pretty dull but the readings were normally pretty interesting.
This is a really interesting class, but be prepared for a slightly unstructured ride!
the material is really interesting, but it matters who the prof is. definitely shop it!

This course looks at contemporary responses to issues revolving around the mind-body problem. It is not as glamorous as it sounds, as many of the readings are very technical. The course draws on a few different approaches to analytic philosophy, which can make it both exciting and demanding. I can't really recommend it except for philosophy majors who have taken multiple philosophy classes.
